Preconditions:
The "days" array must not be null.
The "costs" array must not be null.
The "days" array must contain at least one element.
The "costs" array must contain exactly three elements.
The elements in the "days" array must be in ascending order.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the minimum number of dollars needed to travel every day.
The returned value should be greater than or equal to zero.
The returned value should be the minimum cost among the available options.
The method should not modify the "days" array.
The method should not modify the "costs" array.
The method should not modify the "index" parameter.
The method should not modify the "goodUntil" parameter.